cs.LG, cs.DS, cs.AI, cs.GT, cs.SI 

The paper proposes an algorithm for the adversarial combinatorial multi-armed bandit problem, which is a problem in machine learning and decision making. The algorithm uses a compressed representation of the decision set, which is a data structure commonly used in computer science. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also involves game theory (cs.GT) and optimization on networks (cs.SI), which are relevant sub-categories.
